												<h1>Coming Soon: Multi-Factor Authentication for i4 Server Access</h1>
												<p>Starting <strong>Month, Day, 2018</strong>, Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) will be required to access the i4 server. Introducing MFA creates an additional level of security that will help safeguard NYU and you from cyber threats.</p>
                                                <p>Once rolled out, all i4 account holders will need to confirm their identity with an MFA enrolled mobile device after accessing the server with their NetID and password.</p>
												<h2>Alternative Web Hosting Services</h2>
                                                <p>You should already be <a href="http://start.nyu.edu/" style="color: #57068c;">enrolled in MFA</a>, but we encourage you to take this time to verify your mobile device is a registered MFA device with the Duo Mobile app installed.</p>
                                            </td>
                                        </tr>
